				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Fading Memories<a name="30761"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 26 04 9:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, a few observations:
<br />

<br />
#1.  You can be moving when you activate it.  I absolutely guarantee this.
<br />

<br />
#2.  Make sure you understand what it does.  It does 2 things and only 2 things.  A)  It takes you off every hate list in the zone; and B)  It makes you invisible.
<br />

<br />
#3.  What it doesn't do is prevent a mob from re-agroing you.  Mobs will re-agro you if A) they see inviso; or B) you do something to piss them off -- say, one of your chants ticks over and does another round of damage, or a song you left running hits them again.
<br />

<br />
#4.  The other thing it doesn't do is wipe your group from any hate lists.  So, for example, if your healer heals you, and then you fade, YOU come off the agro list but the healer doesn't.
<br />

<br />
#5.  All the things that customarily break inviso will break the inviso from fade as well.  This can result in agro if you're near a KOS mob.  Starting a song = no inviso = agro.  Attack on = no inviso = agro.  Etc.
<br />

<br />
If this doesn't solve your problem, please be more specific about what's going wrong for you.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
